    <note>Zhang(2) Fu [336] His ancestors moved from Jianning, Pucheng xian, first to Hangzhou, Yanguan (modern Haining) county and then  to Wuzhou, Yongkang xian at the beginning of the dynasty. Fu was the first to establish the fortunes of his family (qijia) in this branch of the lineage by obtaining a jinshi degree. Fu's son, Shi [3187], left home to become the heir of his paternal uncle, Zhang(2) Zhu [3183]. Chen Liang, WJ, 26.1a-5a, 27.4a; XNYL, 199.17a. CBD, 3, 2074.</note>
